tores each insight via `AiSuggestionService.storeSuggestion()` with `planId=planId`, `userId=plan.ownerUserId`, `teamId=plan.teamId`, `weekStartDate=plan.weekStartDate`, and `suggestion_type='PERSONAL_INSIGHT'`. This is called from two places:\n  1. **On plan lock** тАФ `LockService.lockPlan()` calls `insightGenerationService.generatePersonalInsightsAsync(planId)` (hook added in step-5). The `@Async` annotation ensures it doesn't block the lock transaction.\n  2. **Daily scheduled job** тАФ `generateDailyInsights()` iterates all teams, generates team insights, and also generates personal insights for each LOCKED plan in the current week that doesn't already have PERSONAL_INSIGHT rows (idempotency check via `findByPlanIdAndSuggestionType(planId, \"PERSONAL_INSIGHT\")`). This catches plans that were locked while Pinecone/LLM was unavailable.\n- `@Async public void generatePersonalInsightsAsync(UUID planId)` тАФ Thin async wrapper that calls `generatePersonalInsights(planId)` inside a try/catch (graceful degradation). This is the method LockService calls.\n- Add \"TEAM_INSIGHT\" and \"PERSONAL_INSIGHT\" type constants to AiContext.\n\nCreate prompt templates:\n- `backend/src/main/resources/prompts/team-insight.txt`\n- `backend/src/main/resources/prompts/personal-insight.txt`\n\nUpdate `StubAiProvider.java` to handle TEAM_INSIGHT and PERSONAL_INSIGHT with canned responses.\n\nCreate `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/InsightGenerationServiceTest.java`:\n- Unit test with mocked dependencies.\n- Test team insight generation stores correct number of suggestions with teamId and weekStartDate set.\n- Test personal insight generation stores with planId, userId, teamId, weekStartDate set.\n- Test personal insight idempotency (skips if suggestions already exist for the plan).\n- Test unavailable Pinecone skips gracefully.\n- Test scheduled job iterates teams and generates both team + personal insights.",
