-      "description": "Create `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/EmbeddingService.java`:\n- Spring `@Service` with constructor injecting `@Value(\"${ai.openrouter.api-key:}\")` apiKey, `@Value(\"${ai.openrouter.base-url:https://openrouter.ai/api/v1}\")` baseUrl, `@Value(\"${ai.embedding.model:openai/text-embedding-3-small}\")` model, and `ObjectMapper`.\n- Uses `java.net.http.HttpClient` (same pattern as `OpenRouterAiProvider`).\n- Public method `float[] embed(String text)` that POSTs to `{baseUrl}/embeddings` with body `{model, input: [text]}`, parses the response JSON to extract the `data[0].embedding` array as `float[]`.\n- Public method `boolean isAvailable()` that returns false when apiKey is blank.\n- All errors caught and logged; returns empty `float[0]` on failure (graceful degradation).\n\nCreate `backend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/EmbeddingServiceTest.java`:\n- Unit test (Mockito, no Spring context needed since we test the class directly).\n- Mock the HttpClient to return a canned JSON response with a 1536-dim vector.\n- Verify request format (correct URL, headers, body JSON structure).\n- Test blank API key returns empty array.\n- Test HTTP error returns empty array.\n- Follow existing test patterns from `OpenRouterAiProviderTest.java` тАФ plain JUnit 5 + AssertJ.",
