-      "title": "Create SemanticIndexService.java + event-driven indexing hooks",
-      "description": "Create `backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/SemanticIndexService.java`:\n- Spring `@Service`.\n- Constructor injects `PineconeClient`, `EmbeddingService`, `ChunkBuilder`, and relevant repositories (`WeeklyPlanRepository`, `WeeklyCommitRepository`, etc.).\n- `@Async public void indexEntity(String entityType, UUID entityId)` тАФ Loads the entity from the appropriate repository, calls ChunkBuilder to build chunk, calls EmbeddingService to embed, calls PineconeClient to upsert (namespace = org ID looked up via team тЖТ org). Catches all exceptions (graceful degradation).\n- `@Async public void deleteEntity(String entityType, UUID entityId)` тАФ Calls PineconeClient.deleteByIds.\n- `@Scheduled(cron = \"0 0 3 * * *\") public void dailySweepReindex()` тАФ For plans updated in the last 48 hours, re-index all their commits, scope changes, carry-forwards. This catches anything that failed during async indexing. Guarded by `PineconeClient.isAvailable()`.\n- All methods check `PineconeClient.isAvailable()` before doing work.\n\nAdd indexing hooks (direct calls at the end of service methods, not Spring Events as specified):\n- `CommitService.java`: after `createCommit()` and `updateCommit()`, call `semanticIndexService.indexEntity(\"commit\", savedCommit.getId())`. Inject SemanticIndexService via constructor (optional dependency тАФ use `@Autowired(required=false)` or just inject and null-check).\n- `ScopeChangeService.java`: after creating a ScopeChangeEvent, call indexEntity(\"scope_change\", event.getId()).\n- `CarryForwardService.java`: after creating a CarryForwardLink, call indexEntity(\"carry_forward\", link.getId()).\n- `ManagerReviewService.java`: after creating a ManagerComment, call indexEntity(\"manager_comment\", comment.getId()).\n- `TicketService.java`: after create/update, call indexEntity(\"ticket\", workItem.getId()).\n- `LockService.java`: after locking a plan, call indexEntity(\"plan_summary\", plan.getId()).\n- `ReconciliationService.java`: after reconcile submit, call indexEntity(\"plan_summary\", plan.getId()).\n\nThe `@Async` annotation on `indexEntity()` ensures these calls don't block the write path. Since `@EnableAsync` was added in step-1, Spring will proxy the calls.\n\nNo separate test file needed for SemanticIndexService in this step тАФ it will be indirectly tested. But ensure existing tests pass since we're modifying service constructors (use `@Autowired(required=false)` or default null for the new SemanticIndexService dependency so existing mocked tests don't break).",
